{0 day11-doc}

Documentation generation pipeline using odoc. {!Day11_doc.Generate} orchestrates
the two-pass process: compile (produce [.odoc] files per package) then
link (cross-reference and generate HTML), with tool builds integrated
into the unified DAG for parallel execution. {!Day11_doc.Doc_deps} determines
whether a package needs separate compile and link phases by comparing
its dependency graphs with and without [{post}] deps. {!Day11_doc.Phase} defines
doc phase and result types. {!Day11_doc.Command} generates the shell commands
for [odoc_driver_voodoo] invocations. {!Day11_doc.Prep} creates the directory
layout expected by the driver, using bind mounts to avoid copying
files from cached build layers. {!Day11_doc.Odoc_store} provides per-package
isolated mounts for odoc output with atomic commit on success.
{!Day11_doc.Sync} distributes generated HTML via rsync. {!Day11_doc.Combine} aggregates
doc layers into a single overlayfs for local viewing. {!Day11_doc.Tool_binaries}
extracts specific tool binaries for bind-mounting into containers.
{!Day11_doc.Tool_layer} manages driver and per-compiler odoc tool layers.
{!Day11_doc.Universe} tracks universe directories for documentation GC.
{!Day11_doc.Doc_meta} is the sidecar metadata for doc layers ([doc.json]),
recording the package name, phase, and dependencies.
{!Day11_doc.Doc_build} provides stateless per-package doc build
primitives (compile, link, doc-all) that take explicit inputs and
produce results — the building blocks for both the DAG executor and
external pipeline systems like OCurrent.

Sits near the top of the dependency hierarchy, depending on
{!page-opam_build}, {!page-opam_layer}, {!page-layer},
{!page-container}, and {!page-exec}.

See {!page-doc_dep_graphs} for the source-of-truth reference on
which dependency closure (build_deps vs doc_deps) each step in the
pipeline consumes, and the per-step layer-mount conventions.

